      Any Suggestions would be nice<br>
Dartmou <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utaluracwnzeylon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talura cwnZeylon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/1/01 2:45:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PGT??</span><hr size=1> You'd probably do better with it in primary (multiple reasons: more likely to proc, as you have to get the dual-wield check to succeed before checking proc; fast off-hand weapon should make dual-wield skill raise quicker) but if you're set on losing the PGT there are quite a few viable items to replace with. You said you have a limited budget, but without knowing how much and which server I doubt any of us could do more than say look for a langseax or crystallized sword or whatever.<br>
My personal suggestion would be to try and find a higher lvel friend who hits Kael, ask him to get you a berserker's sword (I think it's 12/29, magic,lore) or whatever the axe there is (I think it was 8/22, magic,lore). Both are considered pretty weak items for the level you need for them, but at lower levels they can be nice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udartmou2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dartmou2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/1/01 7:47:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PGT??</span><hr size=1> I am on bristlebane and am making aroun 10pp an hour in LOIO.  Are leangaxes that good?<br>
I almost but a crystalized sword today for 200pp is that a good price or should i have offerd like 150pp? thanks for replying. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umintzyfresch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mintzy Fresch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/1/01 11:15:22 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/uryvichk/mintzy.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PGT??</span><hr size=1> First of all, the PGT is no shameful thing to have until your 20s when the proc becomes kinda worthless. My PGT served me well. Post-20, I'd definitely recommend a Crystallized Sword (or Icetooth's Claws); I have absolutely no complaints about mine (I'm a late-20s warrior and rising quick), and it's a good buy for the price. Ratio's better than a yak IIRC, that'll blow your mind. Not as fast but it taunts well and it's generally cheap.<br>
<br>
A Langseax isn't a bad choice either, but depending on your server it could be very very rare or common as dirt... I've never seen one on Rallos Zek, ever, but on some servers they're just lying around.<br>
<br>
Another excellent choice is the Velium Battle Axes from Icewell Keep. 8/28 isn't great, but it isn't terrible either if you need something with a bit more kick, and if you physically *go* to IK, you can usually get one or two, free. Can't beat that, and if nothing else you can get a few and sell them - buy yourself something else if you want even better, which is certainly plausible.<br>
<br>
Definitely look for Crystallized Swords or Langseaxs, and auction for them by name instead of asking for 'a 1hs' - your results will be much better. And try to get the CS for 150-200pp, negotiate low. Use your PGT as collateral too, it still fetches a respectable price despite saturation here on RZ.<br>
<br>
-Mintzy Fresch,<br>
Rallos Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utaluracwnzeylon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talura cwnZeylon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/2/01 8:50:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PGT??</span><hr size=1> Hehe..always try to negotiate down. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Keep your ears open, and if you have friends/a guild see if they have any current price checks...you'll find true bargains occasionally, and sometimes you'll run across people like me who rarely/never go to bazaar zones and thus try to get 3-6 month old prices for stuff. *blush*<br>
If you're smart, you'll pick up a weapon because it works good and not because it &quot;looks cool&quot;.  Shopping around is the big thing...don't jump into a deal half-assed. If they're pushing you to buy it because it's a &quot;good deal&quot; chances are they're desperate to dump a crap item off for more than it's worth.<br>
GL <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/2/01 9:59:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PGT??</span><hr size=1> /agree<br>
